# Structured Logging & Diagnostic Export

> 📖 **Complete Guide**: `.prot/pillars/q4-resilience-observability/pillar-r/observability.md`
> JSON semantic logging with traceId propagation for end-to-end observability

## Quick Check (30 seconds)
- [ ] All logs use JSON format (not console.log or plain text)
- [ ] Every log includes: `event`, `timestamp`, `traceId`, `level`
- [ ] Event names use semantic IDs (`domain:entity:action`)
- [ ] TraceId propagates through all layers (view → service → adapter → Lambda)
- [ ] Log files stored as JSONL (one JSON object per line)
- [ ] CloudWatch Logs configured with retention policy
- [ ] Structured logger library used (pino, winston, or custom)

## Core Pattern: JSON Semantic Logging

**Golden Rule**: Never use console.log in production. Always use structured logger.

```typescript
// Step 1: Setup structured logger (kernel/telemetry/logger.ts)
import pino from 'pino';

export const logger = pino({
  level: process.env.LOG_LEVEL || 'info',
  formatters: {
    level(label) {
      return { level: label };
    },
  },
  timestamp: () => `,"timestamp":"${new Date().toISOString()}"`,
});

// Step 2: Log with semantic event IDs
import { logger } from '@/kernel/telemetry';

export async function processOrder(orderId: OrderId, traceId: string) {
  logger.info({
    event: 'order:processing:start',  // domain:entity:action
    orderId,
    traceId,
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
  });

  try {
    const result = await chargePayment(orderId);

    logger.info({
      event: 'order:payment:success',
      orderId,
      traceId,
      paymentId: result.paymentId,
      amount: result.amount,
    });
  } catch (error) {
    logger.error({
      event: 'order:payment:failed',
      orderId,
      traceId,
      error: error.message,
      stack: error.stack,
    });
    throw error;
  }
}

// Step 3: Query logs by traceId
// cat logs/2026-02-05.jsonl | jq 'select(.traceId == "trace-abc123")'
```

**Why semantic event IDs?**
- ✅ Searchable: `jq 'select(.event | startswith("order:"))'`
- ✅ Hierarchical: `order:payment:success` vs `order:payment:failed`
- ✅ Self-documenting: Event name describes what happened
- ✅ Filterable: Group by domain, entity, or action

