## Querying Logs

### Local: jq Queries

```bash
# Get all logs for a traceId
cat ~/.myapp/logs/2026-02-05.jsonl | \
  jq 'select(.traceId == "trace-abc123")' | \
  jq -s 'sort_by(.timestamp)'

# Get all error events
cat ~/.myapp/logs/2026-02-05.jsonl | \
  jq 'select(.level == "error")'

# Get all events for specific domain
cat ~/.myapp/logs/2026-02-05.jsonl | \
  jq 'select(.event | startswith("order:"))'

# Follow a flow from start to finish
cat ~/.myapp/logs/2026-02-05.jsonl | \
  jq 'select(.traceId == "trace-abc123") | {time: .timestamp, event, level}' | \
  jq -s 'sort_by(.time)'
```

### CloudWatch Logs Insights

```sql
-- Find all errors for a traceId
fields @timestamp, event, error
| filter traceId = "trace-abc123"
| filter level = "error"
| sort @timestamp desc

-- Find all events in a flow
fields @timestamp, event, level
| filter traceId = "trace-abc123"
| sort @timestamp asc

-- Count events by type
stats count() by event
| sort count desc

-- Find slow operations
fields @timestamp, event, duration
| filter event = "order:processing:complete"
| filter duration > 1000
| sort duration desc
```

